Al este de la Colonia Huaqueña, en el sector Bretaña o Loma Corazón. Bosque muy húmedo Montano. Bosque primario.

Cordillera del Cóndor region. Río Machinaza watershed, east of Los Encuentros. Steep sandstone ridge, just below Hollín sandstone plateau. Very dense, dwarf scrub vegetation on exposed ridge, most shrubs 2-3 m tall. La Zarza mining concession of Kinross Aurelian Corp., about 2 km southeast of and 600 m above Las Peñas camp.

Cordillera del Cóndor. Reserva Biológica Cerro Plateado. Meseta o tepui de roca arenisca de la Formación Hollín, y filo de arenisca. Suelo arenoso, ácido. Vegetación arbustiva, baja y densa. Primera expedición biológica al Cerro Plateado.
Paramo entre Pindilic y Azogues. Paramo de Chanin, Paramo seco dominado por Puyas.

Cordillera del Cóndor. The Machinaza plateau, one of the highest-elevation Hollín sandstone plateaus in the Cóndor region. About 500 m west of the Ecuador-Peru international border, near end of trail from Paquisha Alto military post. Bare sandstone substrate, or quartzsite sand derived therefrom, very nutrient-poor. Dwarf scrub vegetation, dominated by shrubs to about 1.5 m tall, with occasional small trees to 4 m tall. Vegetation recovering slowly from an extensive burn about 20 years previously, with charred woody stems in abundance on ground.
Cordillera de Nanguipa. Cerro Colorado. About 8 km by air SSE of Nambija, 20 km ESE of Zamora. Highest summit on ridge; quartz rock substrate. Dwarf, dense scrub forest 3-5 m tall.

Cordillera de los Llanganates. Loma 2.5 km W of Cerro Hermoso. Polylepis forest.
Llanganati. Steep slope along Río Topo, immediately SE of Aucacocha. Elfin forest.
